Label: Who is the Custodian?
PlaceHolder: Responsible for the overall value and governance of the asset, including: funding, legal requirements, policy and business rules. This role is typically at a senior executive level.

Label: Who is the Business Owner?
PlaceHolder: Responsible for the day to day decisions regarding the business management, use and outcomes of the asset. Usually has a reporting line to the Custodian.

Label: Who are the Steward(s)?
PlaceHolder: The subject matter experts who work closely with the asset; they are responsible for its collection, operation and maintenance. Usually has a reporting line to the Business Owner.

Label: Who is the Curator?
PlaceHolder: The technical administrators responsible for the architecture, design, maintenance and operation of an asset’s technology components. This role also includes the person in Agency managing vendor relationships.

PlaceHolder: Please provide the name of the Vendor, if one was used.
